    "Therefore, while incorporating insights and expertise from the business world is vital, complete delegation of regulatory authority to businesses poses risks and challenges that would appear to be unethical to accept.",
    "Possible solutions Benefits and problems with previous solutionsSchiff et al. [128] analyze how AI ethics and governance issues are treated in public, private and NGO sectors.",
    "Historically, there are, however, also public-private partnerships that have been pursued, for example in public health.",
    "Such cooperatives hold huge benefits, like the ongoing innovativeness of the business world and the legislation still being accounted for by the public.",
    "At the same time, there are difficulties since the ideals, incentives, and structures of both organizations may be different [114]."
